Gaupol 0.27
===========

 [X] Fix dialog paddings with GTK+ 3.14
 [X] Fix text view line length display with GTK+ 3.14
 [X] Hide tabs when only one tab is open
 [X] Expand tabs to fill window width, use 24 characters at minimum
 [X] Pack video player toolbar and seekbar horizontally
 [X] Avoid column resizing upon opening file
 [X] Fix "IndexError: list index out of range" when undoing or redoing
     by holding Ctrl+(Shift)+Z pressed
 [X] Remove use of deprecated stock items, Gtk.Alignment,
     gi.types.Boxed.__init__ and non-transient dialogs
 [X] Update Spanish translation (Carlos Mella)

Gaupol 1.0
==========

 * Bump GTK+ dependency to 3.12
   - Use Gtk.Widget's margin-start instead of margin-left
 * Bump GTK+ dependency to 3.14
   - Make zebra coloring faster by using CSS as since 3.14 we can rely
     on certain basic named colors being available
     o http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=709617#c1
     o http://git.gnome.org/browse/gtk+/tree/gtk/resources/theme/Adwaita/_colors-public.scss
 * Apply new GNOME goals
   - http://wiki.gnome.org/Initiatives/GnomeGoals/PortToGMenu
   - http://wiki.gnome.org/Initiatives/GnomeGoals/PortToGtkApplication
   - http://mail.gnome.org/archives/gtk-devel-list/2013-July/msg00016.html
   - http://wiki.gnome.org/HowDoI/
 * Use a header bar or do something else about dialogs with only close
   and maybe help buttons in the dialog action area (at least preferences,
   search, spell-check)
 * Allow using multiple dictionaries for spell-check
 * Add a GStreamer-based audio waveform display
